        </GroupBox>
        <GroupBox x:Name="groupBox1" Header="How to Use" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="566" Margin="33,42,0,0" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="754" FontSize="20">
            <TextBlock x:Name="textBlock1" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="10,25,10,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" FontSize="16"><Run Text="To use RandImg, start by selecting a folder to search images from. This can be done by clicking &quot;Add&quot; at the bottom of the window or dragging and dropping folders in. RandImg will search for images in these folders as well as images in sub-folders inside of them."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="You can then set some options for RandImg. Window type will determine whether it starts fullscreen or as a resizable window. Autoplay lets RandImg cycle through images automatically."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="You can filter through the image files displayed using the search and exclude pattern fields. These will search based on single character tags in the file name between two '~' symbols. For example, using a search pattern of &quot;3&quot; would show an image named &quot;testimage~123~.png&quot; and using an exclude patten of &quot;1&quot; would prevent it from being "/><Run Text="shown"/><Run Text=". The difference between the &quot;and&quot; and &quot;or&quot; versions of search patten are relevant when multiple tags are used. Using a search pattern of &quot;14&quot; would show &quot;testimage~123~.png&quot; for the &quot;or&quot; field but not for the &quot;and&quot; field. You can mix and match these three fields to perform more specific searches. Leaving all of these fields blank will not filter the output images."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="These settings can be saved to a file using the &quot;Save Presets&quot; button at the bottom right and can be loaded by pressing the &quot;Load Presets&quot; button. Presets can also be loaded by dragging a presets file onto the main window."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="After the settings are set and the files are selected, press start to start showing images. Controls for RandImg while running are shown to the right."/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>
        </GroupBox>

